subSubSection.paragraph:
Pedipalps
: Femur with VI, DI, and DE carinae complete, granular; VM present in proximal half of segment; VE vestigial (
fig. 19E
); dorsal surface with few scattered granules; internal surface with prominent granules medially; ventral surfaces smooth. Patella with DI and VI carinae complete, granular; DPP and VPP with prominent spiniform granules proximally (
fig. 19F
). Chela robust, with relatively elongated fingers; surfaces smooth and acarinate (
fig. 19B–D
); fixed finger of adult ♂ strongly curved and lobed, creating distinct proximal gap with movable finger when fingers are closed, which is weakly developed in 
♀
. Movable finger, median denticle row comprising six subrows; one or two internal and external accessory denticles flanking subrows II and III; distal three subrows without external accessory denticles (
fig. 20F
).
